@lupesko  The CPU numbers are correct. I reran the experiments for Cpu and found similar numbers. 


The higher latencies is attributed to higher number of requests coming in. We ran 100 concurrent workers sending 100 request each to 32 vCPU in P3.8xlarge. In case of CPU(c5.2xlarge) , the number of vCPUs is only 8 whereas the request rate remains same and hence we got the backlog and higher latencies. Apart from that some of the work gets shared by GPU in p3.8xlarge leading to better latencies. 

We tried the same experiments with 25 concurrent workers sending 100 request each to the CPU instance and the latencies were comparable to that for 10000 requests for GPU instance. So, it is basically the number of backlog requests leading to high latencies

