@PabloLefort I think you're code will fail if the address starts with any byte value or values which start with `0` when hex encoded.  Try the following.

```
def normalize_32_byte_hex_address(value):
    as_bytes = eth_utils.to_bytes(hexstr=value)
    return eth_utils.to_normalized_address(as_bytes[-20:])
```

Haven't tested the code above but it should get you moving in the right direction.

